This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on grammatical error correction. The use of neural network models also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper's focus on continuous space representation of words and non-linear mappings suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the use of contextual information from the source sentence suggests that it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category as well.
